consensus text: Buffy blood Part of the red coagulum washed from
colouring matter and made quite white called N[superscript]o[/superscript]. 1. Part of the
buffy coat well washed & called N[superscript]o[/superscript] 2. A spleen shaken in
water & the colouring matter washed off. the mass of globules ob -
tained were of a duly red colour & called N[superscript]o[/superscript]. 3
They were all insoluble in alcohol with similar appearances
also in Mur acid _ equally soluble in alkali & affected by acids
the voltaic battery & other agents in a way perfectly alike in each.
8 oz give 226 insoluble in alcohol. and 124 sol in alcohol
cream of lime added to the 124 liberated much ammonia & when filterd
the substance weighed only 100 _ 20 oz contain 875 gr solid
matter [unclear]i.e[/unclear] Salts 230 _ Albumen gelatine mucus &c 394 _ Urea
